<HEADLINE> Germany Urges All Its Nationals to Leave D.R. Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The German Foreign Ministry Friday
urged all German nationals to leave the Democratic Republic of the
Congo (D.R. Congo) as soon as possible due to the worsening
situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Friday, the German Foreign Ministry said
that the latest developments in the Congo were the cause for great
concern, which might force Germany to close its embassy in
Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
According to official estimates, about 180 German nationals,
including 26 embassy staff, still remain in the African country.
</P>
<P>
Fighting between rebel forces and government forces loyal to
President Laurent Kabila has been intensified since Thursday with
the rebels reportedly having captured the Inga hydro-electricity
dam and deprived Kinshasa of electricity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
