<HEADLINE> Shanxi to Host '98 Commodity Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
will host the '98 Commodity Fair from September 18 through 23 in
the city of Taiyuan, capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which will be held in an area covering some 20,000
square meters and is expected to have more than 600 booths, was
organized by the provincial government to promote the province's
economic and technological cooperation with the rest of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Brand-name goods from both Shanxi and elsewhere will be
displayed at the fair, and a dozen of the province's major
enterprises will be publicizing their products.
</P>
<P>
There will also be opportunities for the ownerships of some
enterprises to be rented or transferred; and scientific
achievements also will be exchanged or transferred.  
</P>
