<HEADLINE> Chinese President Inspects Floods-Ravaged Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- All of the country's forces
should make continued and concerted efforts to support civilians
and soldiers who are standing on the flood-fighting front lines
until a final victory is achieved, President Jiang Zemin urged
today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, pointed out that
flood-fighting on the Yangtze River has reached a crucial
moment when problems may easily appear and carelessness is
liable to cause huge losses.
</P>
<P>
He said that outstanding achievements have already been made in
fighting the raging floods in Fujian, Guangxi, Hunan, Hubei,
Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu, Heilongjiang, Jilin, and Inner Mongolia
since mid-June.
</P>
<P>
During the unprecedented struggle against the Yangtze floods, a
large number of civilians and soldiers have scored a vital victory
by defending the levee for more than 40 days and withstanding five
flood crests, he added.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang demanded that leaders at all levels place
great importance on the flood-fighting effort and give it top
priority, and told them they are all responsible for the effort.
</P>
<P>
Each locality and concerned department and forces from
everywhere should firmly obey orders from the State Flood Control
and Drought Relief Headquarters, he said.
</P>
<P>
The People's Liberation Army should play the role of shock
troops, overcoming fatigue and sharpening vigilance to make new
contributions, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called for timely efforts to evacuate the people in
dangerous places and ensure they are provided with food, boiled
water, housing, and access to doctors, adding that attention must
be paid to epidemic prevention and public security.
</P>
<P>
Another task is to restore production and rebuild homes, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The president said that immediately after the flooding,
efficient measures will be taken to build water-control facilities
and raise the capacity for flood prevention.
</P>
<P>
Water control efforts are very important for maintaining social
order and invigorating the nation. Floods, a hidden trouble
threatening the lives, property and safety of the people, should
arouse high concern from the whole Party, he noted.
</P>
<P>
On his journey from Xiantao City to Wuhan this morning, Jiang
also inspected two perilous sections, Longwangmiao and
Yueliangwan, on the embankment of the Yangtze in Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Jiang were Wen Jiabao, vice-premier of the State
Council and head of the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters; Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission; and Zeng Qinghong, director of the General Office of
the CPC Central Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
