<HEADLINE> 27 Civilians Massacred in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven civilians were
massacred on Thursday night and Friday morning in four separate
attacks in Algeria, news reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed Thursday night in Sidi Bouzid in the
region of Laghouat, 400 kilometers south of Algiers, reports
quoted the Algerian security service as saying.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people were killed over the period in the region of Ain
Defla, 160 kilometers southwest of Algiers, while 11 others were
killed at Sekouma and Sebiri.
</P>
<P>
The security service held "terrorist groups" -- a term used by
the security to mean Islamic militants -- responsible for the
killings. It did not provide further details.
</P>
<P>
A bomb blew up a train running from the western port city of
Oran to Algiers on Wednesday, killing seven people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
