<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-14 15:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Condemns Taliban for Holding Iranian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Turkey Friday strongly condemned
Afghanistan's Taliban forces for holding 11 Iranian staff members
at the Iranian Consulate in Mazari-e-Sharif and a reporter since
last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Turkish Foreign Ministry urged the Taliban
forces not to prevent foreigners who want to leave Afghanistan
from departing, saying that Turkey expects the Taliban forces to
set free the Iranian diplomats and the reporter with the official
Iranian news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey condemns all kinds of terrorist activities such as
holding civilians hostage," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Iran earlier said the Taliban forces captured the Iranian
diplomats and the IRNA correspondent residing in Mazari-e-Sharif,
the main stronghold of the opposition Northern Alliance, on
Saturday when they took control of the city.
</P>
<P>
However, the Taliban stated that they did not hold any Iranian
diplomats and the Iranian consulate general in Mazari-e-Sharif had
been evacuated when their forces reached.
</P>
<P>
Tehran argued that available evidence proved that the Iranian
diplomats and reporter were in the hands of the Taliban and were
transferred to Qandahar, the group's headquarters in southern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran has accused the Taliban of violating international laws
and norms and held Pakistan, the Taliban's main supporter,
responsible for the safety and release of the Iranian diplomats.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
