<DOCNO> XIE19980814.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fifth Flood Crest Brings No Hike in Wuhan's Water Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The fifth flood crest of the
Yangtze River this season is passing Wuhan, capital of central
China's Hubei Province, without causing a rise in the local water
level.
</P>
<P>
Though the water flow increased from 65,600 cubic meters per
second to 65,900 cubic meters per second, the water level dropped
0.01 meters from 2:00 pm to 8:00 pm, according to a local source.
</P>
<P>
Dike breaches and flood-diverting efforts have increased the
capacity for water accumulation, and the water surface of this
section is also broadening, bringing about the decreased water
level, according to water control experts.
</P>
<P>
The fourth flood crest passed the city with a water level of
29.39 meters early in the morning of August 10. The water level
has been dropping slowly since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
