<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary Brings Back Free Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Budapest, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Hungary will implement free
higher education once again for college students, a reversal of
the practice by the former government.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian government decided to implement free education
for students enlisting in colleges after graduation from middle
schools, starting on September 1, the newspaper Nepszava reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that college students must pay their own tuition
if they wanted to pursue advanced studies or turn to other
specialities after graduation from colleges.
</P>
<P>
Hungary for long had free higher education in the past. But
the previous government, carrying economic tightening in 1995,
stipulated that college students must pay tuition.
</P>
<P>
The present government decided to resume free higher education,
which was promised to voters by the major ruling party, the
Fidesz-Hungarian Civic Party (Fidesz).
</P>
<P>
The government also decided to implement some free professional
training programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
