<HEADLINE> Romanian Prime Minister Sees Gains in Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Radu
Vasile says the restructuring of the cabinet is aimed at
increasing Government efficiency, both in terms of the number of
ministers, and in coherence.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister is preparing a government reshuffle which is
expected to take place in the second half of this month.
</P>
<P>
The ruling program of the Vasile cabinet provides for
government restructuring by cutting down on the number of
ministries and secretary of state positions.
</P>
<P>
Vasile told the daily newspaper Cronica Romana on Friday that
"The question of whether some activities and ministries will merge
is still debatable. Different versions are proposed so that an
acceptable pattern may be reached.
</P>
<P>
"The problem is how to merge some ministries in order to
increase their efficiency," the prime minister said, "The final
decision will be exclusively mine."
</P>
<P>
Vasile believed restructuring would begin with cuts in public
spending, and substantial lay-offs would start with the Government
itself.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that all leaders of the coalition parties supported
him.
</P>
<P>
"It is undoubtedly the main achievement of the cabinet I'm
running, I mean not personally mine but the whole team's, the
coalition's finally," he said. 
