<HEADLINE> Philippine President Appoints Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- President Joseph Estrada said
Friday he has chosen a spokesman to do the talking for him so that
he can concentrate on the more pressing tasks in his office.
</P>
<P>
"It's difficult to have my time taken up answering questions
and conducting interviews," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said earlier that he will appoint Jerry Barican, a
veteran and respected journalist, to be his spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Barican said that as spokesman, he will serve as the
president's "microphone" or "loudspeaker" who will amplify and
clarify issues, decisions and policies set by the president and
his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Barican, who will assume his post next week, said that his job
will complement and will never compete with the tasks of the
Office of the Press Secretary.
</P>
<P>
Barican said he will never allow a recurrence of the clash
between the spokesman and the press secretary, which happened
during the previous administration. 
</P>
