<HEADLINE> Old Man Kills Two in Shooting Rampage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A 78-year-old man killed two women
and injured two others with a hunting rifle in a hair dressing
saloon, in the southern French city of Toulouse, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted police as saying that one of
the injured was an 84-year-old woman.
</P>
<P>
Roger Belusca left his house at 9:30 in the morning and crossed
the road heading for the saloon.
</P>
<P>
He shot the proprietress, Marie Josee Tessier, 65, in the chest
at point-blank range as she stood outside the shop.
</P>
<P>
He entered the shop, shot dead a 17-year-old employee, Sandrine
Stawoski, and injured the manager of the shop, Esther Dagouassat,
who is 32, and a client named Odette Martin, 84.
</P>
<P>
Belusca returned to his house and tried to commit suicide by
shooting himself in the face. But he survived and was not in
critical condition, said police.
</P>
<P>
Police did not rule out madness as the cause of Belusca's
action, because he had never had any dispute with the hair
dressing shop. 
</P>
