<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Domestic Exports Show Mixed Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's domestic exports
of major manufactured goods showed mixed performance in the second
quarter of 1998, the latest government figures showed Friday.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports of machinery, equipment,
apparatus, parts and components fell by 12 percent to 8.8 billion
HK dollars (1.1 billion US dollars) in the second quarter, and
that of consumer electrical and electronic products shrank 17
percent to 4.9 billion HK dollars (628 million US dollars),
according to the figures provided by Census and Statistics
Department.
</P>
<P>
But the value of domestic exports of textile products rose 16
percent to 11.8 billion HK dollars (1.5 billion US dollars), and
that of wearing apparel also grew 13 percent to 9.9 billion HK
dollars (1.2 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports of textiles, wearing apparel,
machinery, equipment, apparatus, parts and components, consumer
electronic and electrical products accounted for 72 percent of
Hong Kong's total domestic exports of manufactured goods. 
</P>
