<HEADLINE> Yunnan to Hold Satellite Meeting of Genetic Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China will hold the satellite
meeting of the 18th International Congress of Genetics on August
17 and 18 in Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, with the theme of "Genetics and the Conservation
of Biological Diversity," will hold workshops on the genetic
diversity of animals, plants, micro-organisms and humans.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province has 20,000 species of higher plants and
thousands of vertebrate animal species. To date, it has
established five national nature reserves including the
Xishuangbanna tropical rain forest. Yunnan also has the greatest
number of ethnic groups in China, 16 of whom live only in the
province.
</P>
<P>
About 100 congress participants have already registered for the
meeting, according to the organizing committee of the 18th
International Congress of Genetics.
</P>
<P>
This congress, the largest of its kind in the world, has
attracted more than 2,000 scholars from 54 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
It has also drawn great attention from scientific circles in
Beijing, since it is the first time China will host the
conference. Some of the participants will be invited by the
Ministry of Forests and the Chinese Academy of Science to attend
related symposiums in Beijing soon after the conference adjourns.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scholars working abroad who have returned to attend
the conference will be invited to present talks on genetics at
Beijing University after it concludes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
