<P>
COLOMBO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Liberation Tigers
of the Tamil Eelam (LTTE) hijacked a foreign merchant ship off the
northeastern coast of Sri Lanka Friday, according to informed
sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said gunmen from the LTTE seized a Dubai-owned
merchant vessel with 21 crew members on board, including 16 Indian
nationals.
</P>
