<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The China Foundation for Human
Rights Development donated one million yuan (about 120,000 U.S.
dollars) in money and relief materials to the flood victims in
central and northeast China today.
</P>
<P>
As a non-governmental organization, the Foundation has been
devoted to the development of human rights for several years. The
Foundation itself allocated 500,000 yuan, and received help from two
corporations who donated 500,000 yuan worth of medicines and tents.
</P>
<P>
Huang Hua, honorary chairman of the Foundation, presented the
donation to the Chinese Ministry of Civil Affairs at today's
ceremony.  
</P>
