<HEADLINE> China To Issue Flood-Fighting and Disaster Relief Stamp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Liu Liqing, director of the
State Postal Service Bureau, today announced that his bureau plans
to issue a special stamp to solicit donations for flood disaster
relief this year.
</P>
<P>
This will be a single stamp scheduled to be issued on September
10 with a postage face value of 50 fen (6 U.S. cents). The stamp
will cost 1 yuan (100 fen) and the entire cost will be turned over
to the concerned departments for the flood relief effort, Liu
said. The State Postal Service Bureau plans to circulate 30 million
of these special donation stamps.
</P>
<P>
Although the issuance of such a stamp usually takes 2 years,
this stamp will be treated as a special case, he said, adding that
the State Postal Service Bureau has made all the necessary
preparations, from the design and printing to transport and sales.
</P>
<P>
China has only issued three sets of stamps attached to
donations since the founding of the People's Republic of China in
1949. The others went to social welfare efforts for children and
the disabled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
