<HEADLINE> Mud-Rock Flow in Flood-Ravaged North China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Flood-besieged Zalantun City in
north Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region in north China was struck
by a sudden mud-rock flow this morning, disrupting and inundating
local houses and affecting 200 to 300 households.
</P>
<P>
Two water columns quickly ran between two hills in the
Xiaobeigou section of the city at 8:30 this morning, followed by a
mud-rock flow which surged toward the city proper, according to a
report from the Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters of
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The mud-rock flow is continuing to advance to the downtown
areas and a local railway line is very likely to be inundated,
said Zhao Fenglin, leader of the city, this evening. 
</P>
