<HEADLINE> Security Beefed Up at U.S. Embassy in Botswana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Increased security
measures were introduced at the United States embassy in Gaborone
Friday, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted embassy spokesman David Franz as saying the
embassy was "adopting a heightened security posture." He said
several non-essential staff were sent home Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The embassy's routine has been made irregular so we present a
less tantalizing target for terrorists," Franz said.
</P>
<P>
The Botswana government has also beefed up security at the
embassy, including the deployment of an armored troop carrier
outside the building.
</P>
<P>
The measures followed last week's bomb blasts at U.S.
embassies in Kenya and Tanzania, which killed more than 250
people and injured over 5,000.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday and Thursday, the U.S. embassy in Mbabane,
Swaziland, received bomb hoaxes. 
