<HEADLINE> China to Host International Tea Cultural Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 China International Tea
Cultural Fair will be held September 15-20 at the National
Agricultural Exhibition Center in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
An official from the event's sponsor, the Society for the
Promotion of Traditional Chinese Culture, said at a press
conference here today that the fair will be the largest of its
kind ever held in China, where the tradition of tea dates back to
the Tang Dynasty (618-907).
</P>
<P>
The fair will provide a chance for Chinese and foreign
specialists and businessmen to conduct cultural exchanges as well
as industrial and trade cooperation, the official said.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day fair, about 300 enterprises from 14
countries and regions worldwide will exhibit more than 1,000
varieties of tea-leaves, tea-sets, pottery tea accessories, and
tea manufacturing and packaging equipment, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
The fair will include a series of tea-related cultural
activities such as academic seminars, fashion shows, and painting
and art exhibitions, he said, adding that a number of cultural
troupes from China, Japan and the Republic of Korea will perform
their traditional tea ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has issued a set of commemorative postage materials
including stamps, booklets, and first-day envelopes depicting
Chinese tea culture for the fair," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
