<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province to Intensify Fight Against Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
has pledged to intensify the fight against smuggling activities as
part of an effort to stabilize the province's economic order.
</P>
<P>
"The large amounts of oil products smuggled into the country
have brought about a considerable drop in the price of domestic
oil products, and caused many domestic oil plants to operate at a
loss," said a senior official.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 and the first half of this year, Lanzhou Customs
prevented 28 cases of smuggling involving some 340 million yuan in
goods.
</P>
<P>
In order to strike hard at the smugglers, the province has
recently set up a comprehensive anti-smuggling office comprised
of personnel from 21 related government departments.
</P>
<P>
"Priority will be given to a crackdown on the smuggling of
automobiles, sheep's wool and narcotics," the official said.
</P>
