stand in the oil-rich Central Asian region, if Washington reaches
a deal with the Taliban, which wishes to be recognized by the
United Nations as the legitimate government of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Talibans are now controlling more than three-fourths of the
territory of Afghanistan. 
