<HEADLINE> Across-Straits Shipping Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Approximately 750 ships sailed
across the Taiwan Straits, loading 117,100 containers, in the
first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ships include 371 from Taiwan to east China's Fujian
province, with 53,400 containers, and 374 from Fujian to Taiwan,
with 63,700 containers.
</P>
<P>
From April last year, when the two sides of the Taiwan Straits
started direct shipping at selected ports on a trial basis, to the
end of last March, 1,286 ships with 165,197 containers sailed
across the straits.
</P>
<P>
Twelve companies have been approved to conduct the shipping. So
far nine of them opened their across-straits business, who put
into use nine ships with a total shipping capacity of 2,736
containers.  
