<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close One Percent Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stockmarket
finished more than one percent higher Friday as Hong Kong stocks
rallied and optimism built that Wall Street might bounce back
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
At the close of trade, the benchmark all ordinaries index was
27.8 points firmer at 2,569.0.
</P>
<P>
"It was very strong in the end ... helped by the fact that Hang
Seng is five and a half percent higher (at 4 PM, Friday,
Australian Eastern Standard Time)," Nevitts broker Steve Mayne
said.
</P>
<P>
Mayne said there was also some bargaining hunting in the
banking and resources stocks, helped by commodity prices which
were generally stronger overnight.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index rose 53.9 points to 4,548.8 while the
all resources index added 6.0 points to 965.4 points.
</P>
<P>
The banking index stacked on 60.3 points to 5,750.5 with
National Australia Bank leading the way, climbing 41.4 cents to
21.954 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Commonwealth Bank of Australia shares stacked on 25.6 cents at
19.956 Australian dollars. Westpac bank climbed six cents to 9.90
Australian dollars but ANZ bank tumbled 12 cents to 9.54
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector, BHP shed 12 cents to 12.78 Australian
dollars, and Rio Tinto dipped 16.4 cents to 17.536 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the gold sector, the index rose 15.4 points to 971.0 points
while the gold price added 2.40 U.S. dollars an ounce to 284.70
U.S. dollars an ounce Friday.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 345.03 million shares worth 739.04
million U.S. dollars with rises outnumbering falls 545 to 478.
</P>
</TEXT>
