<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar tracked
the Japanese yen higher Friday in Sydney, but still lost almost
half a U.S. cent this week.
</P>
<P>
Rothschild Australia Treasury Manager Paul Macarounas said
trade was "erratic" during the local session with both the yen and
the Australian dollar swinging in a reasonably tight range.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the local unit was changing hands at 59.60 U.S.
cents, up from 59.14 U.S. cents late Thursday. It closed last
Friday at 60.18 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
The yen was underpinned Friday by lingering fears that the
Japanese central bank would intervene to support the Asian
currency at the expense of the greenback.
</P>
<P>
Craig James, chief economist of Colonial State Bank, said
upside for the Australian dollar remained capped by weakness in
the Japanese yen as well as commodity prices.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was buying 86.53 Japanese yen from 86.91
yen at the close, 1.0643 German marks from 1.0600 marks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
