<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Friday as players were
encouraged by the stronger Japanese yen which boosted regional
bourses.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index added 1.25
points to 327.98, the all-share Emas Index gained 0.07 of a point
to 84.44, the Industrial Index was 5.37 points higher at 686.68
while the Second Board Index dropped 0.72 of a point to 77.32.
</P>
<P>
Losers edged gainers 325 by 246 while 171 counters were
unchanged and 181 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 117.103 million shares worth 181.254
million ringgit (43.362 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The mainboard volume decreased to 113.756 million shares worth
177.896 million ringgit (42.559 million U.S. dollars) from 115.343
million shares valued at 197.442 million ringgit (47.234 million
U.S. dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover dropped to 3.347 million shares worth
3.357 million ringgit (803,000 U.S. dollars) from Thursday's 3.738
million shares valued at 3.966 million ringgit (948,000 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals contracted to 919,000 shares worth 2.556
million ringgit (611,000 U.S. dollars) from 4.821 million shares
valued at 11.961 million ringgit (2.861 million U.S. dollars) on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Talk that Bank of Japan is checking the rates after the
government's assertion that it would intervene in the Forex market
to support the yen propelled the currency to a firmer 144-level to
the US dollar.
</P>
<P>
With regional markets looking at Japan for directions, the
improved yen boosted regional currencies and stock markets and
shoved aside worries over Russia's financial problem.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.015
million shares traded, industrial products 13.159 million shares,
construction 6.206 million shares, trading/services 45.876 million
shares, infrastructure 1.063 million shares, finance 17.346
million shares, hotels 1.296 million shares, properties 10.034
million shares, plantation 6.295 million shares, mining 214,000
shares, trusts 206,000 shares, closed/fund 55,000 shares and loans
4.988 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
