<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Korea to Grant Amnesty 7,007 Prisoners Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 14 (Xinhua) -- South Korea Friday announced that
it will grant amnesty to 7,007 jailbirds Saturday when the nation
marks the 50th anniversary of its founding.
</P>
<P>
The special presidential pardon will be granted to the 7,007
ranging from corrupt beaurocrats and businessmen to dissidents, from
former politicians to former generals, from election violators to
former bankers convicted on bribery charges.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 2,174 prisoners, including 103 sentenced under the
National Security Law and 77 foreign prisoners will be released across
the country Saturday morning while the remaining 4,833 will have
suspended prison sentences scrapped or commuted.
</P>
<P>
By freeing thousands of corrupt beaurocrats, dissidents, and other
prisoners, the government hopes to reconcile with the past while
creating consensus for the future, Justice Minister Park Sang-cheon
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The government hopes that this will serve as an occasion to rally
the whole nation to rebuild the country,'' Park said.
</P>
<P>
In South Korea, it is customary for the government to grant a
special amnesty to "exemplary prisoners'' on major national holidays.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
