<HEADLINE> China to Invite Export Quota Tenders Via the Web </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China is working hard to
prepare for the late September establishment of a website to
invite tenders for the 1999 passive quota for textile products.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC)
concluded a simulated tender offering via the web Thursday in
preparation for the actual offering in September.
</P>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, referreed to the establishment of the web as a major
aspect of reform and an exhibition of just, fair, open and
transparent principles for quota administration. He said that the
practice will reduce errors and further improve the efficiency of
standardized quota administration.
</P>
<P>
The results of the simulated tender, which commenced in late
July and ended on Thursday, was announced nationwide via the China
International Electronic Commerce Web.
</P>
<P>
The practice, if proven successful, will be used for export
quotas for all types of commodities, according to a MOFTEC
official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
