<HEADLINE> HK Aims for Six Golds at Asian Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The first Asian Indoor
Cycling Championships will be held here Sunday with host Hong
Kong aiming at all six gold medals in the artistic events.
</P>
<P>
Over 30 riders from Malaysia, Japan, Macao and Hong Kong will
be competing in the championships, which feature men's and
women's artistic events in both singles and pairs as well as
cycle ball games.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong plays a leading role in promoting the indoor cycling
games in Asia. Organizing Committee Chairman Alfred Li told a p
ress conference Friday that Hong Kong has substantial experience
in organizing international events.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong became the first host other than a European country
to hold the World Championships in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, whose rivals will mainly come from Japan and
Malaysia, hopes to capture all gold medals in all six artistic
events.
</P>
<P>
The double round robin cycle ball games will be participated
in by Japan, Malaysia and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
