<HEADLINE> Prince Seeks Amnesty for Politicians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian deposed First Prime
Minister Prince Ranariddh requested Friday to his father King Norodom
Sihanouk to grant pardon to five politicians who were convicted by
Cambodian military court.
</P>
<P>
Prince asked in a letter to the King to amnesty for his two
generals Nhiek Bun Chhay and Serey Kosal, who last March were
convicted by Phnom Penh military cout.
</P>
<P>
He also requested to pardon the alleged two aborted coup plotter
Prince Norodom Chakrapong, Prince Ranariddh's half brother and Sin
Song, former interior minister, and King's half brother Prince
Sirivuddh.
</P>
<P>
"In the name of Funcinpec party, I would like to request your
permission to grant amnesty for those who were convicted by Phnom Penh
and Battambang courts," Ranariddh said in the letter.
</P>
<P>
But the King replied on the same day that "to grant them amnesty
are depending on the approval of Samdech Hun Sen, if Hun Sen agrees,
I will make a royal decree to pardon them immediately."
</P>
<P>
Prince Sirivuddh convicted by Phnom Penh court in 1995 for charges
of attempting to assassinate Cambodian leader Hun Sen. He was since
then in exile in France.
</P>
<P>
Prince Charkrapong and Sin Song, made a failed coup in 1994 were
sentenced to 20 years in prison, while the two Generals were also
charged with the same span in the prison and Prince Sirivuddh was
sentenced to 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The three convicted politicians are having political asylum in
foreign countries while the two armed men are leading resistant
movement against government forces along northern Cambodia-Thai
border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
