<HEADLINE> 13 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Turkish troops have killed 13
Kurdish rebels in latest operations in southeastern Turkey, a
government statement said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The office of Emergency Regional Rule said in a statement that
the 13 members of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were
killed in operations carried out in Van province, Sirnak province,
Diyarbakir province, Siirt province and Unceli province.
</P>
<P>
There were also three government soldiers killed during the
operations.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that the security forces captured two PKK
members in the provinces of Diyarbakir and Sirnak.
</P>
<P>
Over 35,000 people have been killed in conflicts in
southeastern Turkey since the PKK started a guerrilla war to fight
for autonomy in August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
