<HEADLINE> Pakistan Says Ready for "Meaningful" Talks With India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif on Friday said Pakistan is ready to address all outstanding
issues with India through "meaningful and result-oriented" talks.
</P>
<P>
"We are prepared to address and resolve all outstanding issues
through a meaningful and result-oriented dialogue to enable the
two countries to focus their energies and resources on the
well-being of their peoples," Sharif said in a message to Indian
Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee on the independence day of
India.
</P>
<P>
Islamabad is "desirous of" good neighborly and tension-free
relations with New Delhi, "which will ensure peace and stability
in the region," Sharif said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
