<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Industrial Sector Shows Improvement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector in east
China's Jiangsu Province, one of the nation's economic
powerhouses, has improved noticeably since the start of the third
quarter.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises and private industrial enterprises
with annual sales of over five million yuan each generated a total
industrial output of over 496 billion yuan during the first seven
months of the year, up 11.1 percent on the same period last
year. The growth rate ended 1.8 percentage points higher than the
national average for the period.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate for Jiangsu's industrial output hit 13.5
percent in July, and ranked third nationwide behind Sichuan
Province and Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
A recent analysis indicated improved economic efficiency for
Jiangsu's industrial sector during 1998. The state-owned
industrial sector as a whole had turned losses into profits by the
end of June, with total profits for the January-June period
hitting 290 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
