<HEADLINE> Philippines to Hold Micro-finance Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' Coalition for
Mirco-finance Standards, composed of 69 non-government
organizations, banks, and government and resource agencies, will
hold a national summit in Manila on August 20-21.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, whose major sponsors are the Asian Development
Bank (ADB) and the U.S. Agency for International Development, aims
to promote the understanding and adoption of micro-finance
performance standards, the Manila-based ADB said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Among the topics to be discussed are the state of the
micro-finance, non-government organization (NGO) sector in the
Philippines, performance standards for micro-finance NGOs, and
policy and regulatory environment for micro-finance in the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Micro-finance has been widely recognized to be effective in
transforming disadvantaged individuals into financially
independent entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
In the Philippines alone, more than 4.5 million families live
below the poverty threshold. A considerable number of institutions
now provide a variety of financial services to the poor based on
market-driven and commercial approaches, according to the ADB.
</P>
</TEXT>
