<HEADLINE> Caring For Central China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 5 million flood victims
in central China's Hubei Province are getting proper care, thanks to
government relief efforts and donations coming in from across the
country.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial Civil Affairs Department, the
provincial government has earmarked 146 million yuan for relief
work and the department has received more than 70 million yuan
worth of goods and money that are being used for 11 of the province's
hardest hit areas.
</P>
