<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Boost Electronics Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia aims to earn 4 billion
U.S. dollars from exporting electronic products this year, Antara
News Agency Friday quoted a Trade and Industry Ministry official
as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Our target is not too high considering the sluggish situation
in the domestic market. However, we have the opportunity to
increase our electronics exports to Europe and the United States,
both of which have not been affected by the economic crisis (in
Asia)," director of the ministry's electronic goods division
Ardiansyah Parman said.
</P>
<P>
From January to April, Indonesia already earned 1 billion U.S.
dollars from the export of electronic products. The country earned
3.89 billion U.S. dollars in 1997 and 3.9 billion U.S. dollars in
1996 from electronics exports.
</P>
<P>
To boost exports of this commodity, Parman said, the country's
electronics industry should form corporations or partnerships with
multinational companies. 
</P>
