<HEADLINE> Chinese Cities Enjoying Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The China Environmental
Monitoring Center reported today that the bulk of the country's
cities enjoyed good air quality over the past week.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities including Zhuhai, Guilin, Xiamen and Beihai,
enjoyed excellent air quality between August 7-13, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-three cities, including Xi'an, Shanghai, Beijing and
Wuhan, reported good air quality during the period.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Guangzhou, Shanghai, Hefei and Shenzhen reported
high levels of nitrogen oxide, that of Chongqing, with Guiyang
encountering high sulphur dioxide levels. Various other cities
reported high levels of suspended particles.
</P>
<P>
Taiyuan and Lanzhou were the only two cities reporting slight
air pollution during the week, with both experiencing high levels
of suspended particles.  
</P>
