<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce Deal With China's Largest Grain Terminal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Rolls-Royce announced here today
that it will provide 2 grain loaders for Beiliang Dock in the city
of Dalian in northeast China's Liaoning Province, valued at 6
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
They will be manufactured by Rolls-Royce Caillard Company, a
subsidiary in France, and will be delivered in late 1999 or early
2000.
</P>
<P>
When it is completed early next century, Beiliang will be one
of the largest grain terminals in the world.
</P>
<P>
According to a materials handling representative of Rolls-Royce
in China, the loaders have a handling capacity of 2,000 tons an
hour each and are important for grain handling on the dock.
</P>
<P>
She said the loaders will be mainly built in Dalian and erected
on site under Rolls-Royce supervision.
</P>
<P>
The company has previously supplied material handling equipment
to power stations in Jiangsu and Sichuan provinces. It is also
expected to reach a similar agreement with a dock in the special
economic zone of Shenzhen in Guangdong Province later this
year. 
</P>
