<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Initiates Programs to Help Retirees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The vice-governor of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, Chen Zhenggao, pledged recently that
the province's retirees will be provided with a happy life.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's oldest industrial bases, Liaoning has 2.4
million retirees who have contributed to the founding and
development of new China, he said.
</P>
<P>
To ensure a stable and happy life for the country's former
builders, Chen said, Liaoning has organized more than 10,000
working groups to help them solve various kinds of problems.
</P>
<P>
Those working groups send relief funds or gifts to the retirees
on festivals or birthdays, help them repair their houses or
electrical appliances, and assist poor retirees out of poverty.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, some 10 million yuan (1.2 million US dollars) of
relief funds was distributed among retirees, benefiting more than
80,000 families, the vice-governor said.
</P>
<P>
The province also periodically organizes recreational and
sports activities for the retirees so that they can have physical
exercises.
</P>
<P>
Some one million retirees voluntarily take part in such social
activities as helping maintain traffic order and mediating civil
disputes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
