<HEADLINE> 41 Died of Meningitis in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 41 people in Mozambique
have died of meningitis this year, according to Avertino Barreto,
assistant to Mozambique's National Health Bureau director.
</P>
<P>
A total of 186 meningitis cases have been reported since early
this year, most of which in Nampula and Cabo Delgado provinces in
the northern part of the country, although the first cases were
discovered in Sofala Province in central Mozambique, Barreto
revealed in Maputo Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cases have been reduced as against 894 cases in 1997 and
5291 cases in 1996, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The health authorities have carried out vaccination,
particularly in nurseries, army barracks and schools where people
are concentrated. 
</P>
