<HEADLINE> Beijing Set to Host Int'l Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Beijing International
Tourism Cultural Festival will be held on September 23-27 this
year.
</P>
<P>
The festival will be the third largest international tourism
and cultural exchange festival Beijing has hosted following the
Sino-Japanese Folk Customs Festival in 1992 and the Asian Folk
Customs Week in 1995, according to organizers.
</P>
<P>
The event will feature performances by Chinese and foreign
artists, and both tourism agencies and various airline companies
will offer travel information.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 art troupes will stage performances at the Asian Games
Village in northern Beijing on September 27 -- the World Tourism
Day.
</P>
<P>
The festival will also feature traditional Chinese operas,
morning exercise programs and garments exhibitions presented by
various ethnic groups.  
</P>
