<HEADLINE> Belgian Police Holds Man for Alleged Pedophile Behavior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Belgian police held a director
for a youth summer camp late on Wednesday for alleged pedophile
behavior, local television RTBF reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police detained the 35-year-old man in Londeel after picking up
in a forest three runaway campers who described "surprising
behavior" by the camp director who had previous offenses against
children in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Police did not disclose the identity of the alleged pedophile.
</P>
<P>
The court in Louvain has opened an investigation of the man for
indecent assault on minors with violence and threats.
</P>
<P>
Authorities already evacuated the 18-children camp and said
that the children were in good health and had not been raped. The
youngsters in the camp aged between eight and 14.
</P>
<P>
The news set off another shock wave in the country where an
infamous pedophile, Marx Dutroux, was arrested two years ago
around the same time as he kidnapped six children and killed four
of them. 
</P>
