<HEADLINE> Dolan Wins Individual Medley in US Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Tom Dolan returned to form
to win the 400-meter individual medley at the U.S. National
Swimming Championships in California on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dolan who suffered an asthma attack, finished 14th overall in
the 800-meter freestyle finals Tuesday night as "I just couldn't
breath after 300 meters."
</P>
<P>
But Dolan had no problems two days later, winning the 400
individual medley in 4 minutes 16.33 seconds, more than two
seconds ahead of second-placer Tom Wilkins.
</P>
<P>
"After this morning, I thought I was going to have a real good
swim in the finals," Dolan said.
</P>
<P>
However, Cristina Teuscher failed to make a double win when
she finished second in both the 200 freestyle and 400 individual
medley.
</P>
<P>
Lindsay Benko won the 200 freestyle in 2:00.67. Maddy Crippen
won the 400 individual medley in 4:42.61.
</P>
<P>
Crippen was swimming in her third event of the championships
after taking fifth in both the 200 backstroke and 200 butterfly
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Ugur Taner won the men's 200 freestyle in 1:48.91, nipping
Josh Davis at the finish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
