<HEADLINE> China's Development Bank Signs 5-Year Service Pact with Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of
China (SDB) will provide complete financial services for east
China's Anhui Province in the coming five years, said a bank source.
</P>
<P>
SDB President Chen Yuan said that the move represents the
bank's lastest attempt to improve the service of this
policy-oriented bank and to diversify management of assets.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed earlier this week, SDB will act as a
financial consultant for the province and its enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has been one of SDB's priorities. By the end of July, the
bank's outstanding loans to the province has totaled 14.6 billion
yuan involving 96 projects, mainly power and coal projects, which
accounted for 20 percent and 57 percent of the bank's total to the
province.
</P>
<P>
The bank has promised to offer 7 billion yuan in loans to
Anhui's power sector within the next three to five years mostly
for building of urban and rural electricity power grids.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in addition to financial services for the
infrastructure, basic and high-tech industries, SDB will provide
consultation on the province's adjustment of industrial structure,
enterprise restructuring, stock listings, bond issues, syndicated
loans and finding partners for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The bank, established in 1994, was created to aid the country's
infrastructural projects and basic industries. It has financed 80
percent of the country's key construction projects.
</P>
<P>
SDB approved loans worth 53.9 billion yuan between January and
June, up 24 percent over the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
