<HEADLINE> Typhoon Relieves Drought in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Penny has relieved
serious drought conditions in south China's island province of
Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon, instead of causing disasters, has brought badly
needed rains to the province.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the rains have relieved the province's
drought which began last spring. The drought has affected 72,000
hectares of farmland and caused a drinking water problem for
100,000 local residents.
</P>
<P>
Six cities have induced artificial rains with the help of
Penny.
</P>
<P>
Environmentalists said that over-reclamation of land and
deforestation have been major causes for the long-term drought in
the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
