<HEADLINE> Tax Incentives for Export Industries in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Export industries in Bangkok and
15 surrounding provinces will be exempt from duty on imported
machinery, The Board of Investment of Thailand (BOI) decided
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The BOI hoped that the extra assistance for industries would
encourage foreign businesses to base their production in Thailand,
BOI Secretary-General Staporn Kavitanon was quoted Friday by the
Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The tax waivers would help industries such as leather and
garments, which lacked BOI incentives, Staporn said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ventures without BOI privileges would be allowed to
claim tax rebates on imported raw materials used for making
exports.
</P>
<P>
The BOI would also establish a center to help foreign investors
buy or take over the interests of cash-strapped Thai companies, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
