<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peruvian Troops Surround Intruding Ecuadoran Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran troops that infiltrated
Peru are now surrounded by Peruvian forces, said a Peruvian source
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The source said the Peruvian troops, which were five times
greater in number than the intruders, were only 100 meters distant
from the Ecuadorans.
</P>
<P>
The source added that an opening had been left for the
Ecuadoran troops to retreat to their country.
</P>
<P>
A report, quoted by the press, said the Ecuadoran forces,
composed of about 300 soldiers, had entered through nine border
points 2.8 kilometers into the eastern watershed of the El Condor
mountain range.
</P>
<P>
It added that the Ecuadoran soldiers had not built any kind of
defensive works, which indicates that the infiltration occurred
quite recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
