<HEADLINE> Guangdong Police Crack More Smuggling Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong police cracked more
than 280 smuggling cases involving more than 230 million yuan
(27.71 million U.S. dollars) in the first half of this year,
according to the Guangdong Provincial Public Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The cases involved such items as imported cigarettes,
automobiles, motorcycles, pirated VCDs and counterfeit currency.
</P>
<P>
The frontier bureau of the Guangdong police recently cracked a
case involving the smuggling of 62.64 million yuan (7.546 million
U.S. dollars) in counterfeit Chinese currency, the second largest
case of its kind since the founding of new China in 1949.
</P>
