<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Leaders Express Sympathy to China's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin
Ahmed and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina Thursday expressed deep
shock at the loss of lives and damage to properties in central and
eastern China caused by devastating floods, press reports here
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a message of condolence to Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
Ahmed said, "We express our most sincere condolences and
sympathies to the people of the flood-affected area of China."
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the flood victims would be able to withstand the
natural calamity with patience and fortitude.
</P>
<P>
In a separate message to Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, Hasina
said, "On behalf of the government and the people of Bangladesh
and my own behalf, I convey our condolences and sympathies to the
people of China."
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that the heroic people of China will overcome
this crisis with courage and fortitude," she added. 
</P>
