<HEADLINE> Croatia Delivers Protest to Slovenia on Disputed Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Croatian Deputy Foreign Minister
Vladimir Drobnjak Thursday summoned Slovenian Charge d'Affairs
Bogdan Benko and gave him a note protesting Slovenia's reported
incorporation of four disputed villages into Slovenia's
jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, the note accused Slovenia of
incorporating four villages located on the Croatian side on the
Croatia-Slovenia border.
</P>
<P>
If the reports are true, said the note, the Croatian government
requires a formal explanation from Slovenia on the latter's
"unilateral" and "wholly unacceptable" action, which may be "aimed
at infringing on the territorial integrity of Croatia."
</P>
<P>
Slovenia's reported action is "invalid" and Croatia will
respond accordingly to safeguard its legitimate rights, the note
affirmed. 
</P>
