<HEADLINE> UCI to Clean Cycling of Doping Scandals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The International Cycling Union
(UCI) said in Lausanne on Thursday that it will take measures to
clean the sport of doping scandals which have plagued the Tour de
France this year.
</P>
<P>
After a two-day meeting with riders, team chiefs and race
organizers, the UCI said in a statement it would insist on
frequent medical tests on riders from next year.
</P>
<P>
Besides, it would also take a close look at races to see
whether the more arduous ones should be shortened and would
impose a limit of between 90 and 120 days racing per year for
individual riders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
