<HEADLINE> Seven Bodies Found Near U.S.-Mexican Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Seven bodies have been found
in the Southern California desert, about 90 miles east of San
Diego near the Mexican border, local authorities reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The seven -- five men, a woman and a teenage boy -- probably
died of heat exhaustion and appeared to have been dead for at
least three days, said Bill Strassberger, spokesman for the
Immigration and Naturalization Service.
</P>
<P>
The daytime high temperature is over 38 centigrade degrees in
the area and it was about 42 centigrade degrees Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The assumption was they died of heat exposure," Strassberger
said, adding that they were believed to be illegal immigrants from
neighboring Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Each year, scores of illegal immigrants die attempting to cross
into the United States in the rugged Southern California terrain.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 people are believed to have died so far this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
