<HEADLINE> Tianjin Reports 31 Percent Fixed Assets Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the largest port city
in north China, spent 15.28 billion yuan on fixed assets in the
first half of this year, a 31 percent increase from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Capital construction projects accounted for 7.8 billion yuan,
up 57.9 percent. Industrial fixed assets investment used 7.2
billion yuan from January to June, accounting for 47.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the city continued to increase spending
on the service trade and put 2.8 billion yuan into housing
construction.
</P>
<P>
With the help of 4.79 billion yuan, 43 of the city's 48
construction projects for January to June have started. 
</P>
</TEXT>
