<HEADLINE> Liberty Beats Mystics 88-45 in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Kisha Ford scored 17 of her
season-high 19 points in the second half as the New York Liberty
moved into a first-place tie in the WNBA's Eastern Conference
with an 88-45 rout of the Washington Mystics on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The 43-point margin was New York's largest in its two-year
history. Rebecca Lobo and Sophia Witherspoon each netted 12
points for the Liberty, who have won eight of nine and 11 of 13
home games.
</P>
<P>
The loss was Washington's worst of the season. The Mystics,
with three wins and 24 losses, had a 30-point loss to Charlotte.
The Mystics, who have lost two of three after breaking an 11-game
losing streak, were led by Nikki McCray with 21 points. They are
winless this season in 14 road games and are assured of finishing
with the league's worst record.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty held Washington scoreless for five minutes and
scored 13 straight points to take a 19-4 lead in the first
period. New York beat Washington all four previous times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
