<HEADLINE> Commercial Vehicle Sales Plunge in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Commercial vehicle sales in the
Philippines dropped 38.7 percent to 26,995 units in the first
seven months of this year compared with the year-ago level,
according to the latest industry figures.
</P>
<P>
In a report published here Friday, the Chamber of Automotive
Manufacturers of the Philippines Inc. said that total vehicle
sales during the same period declined 46.1 percent to 49,997 units
from 97,756 units reported a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The chamber earlier reported a 52.8-percent decline in the
sales of passenger cars from January to July this year.
</P>
<P>
The poor performance of the local automotive industry was
blamed on the economic crisis which pushed up interest rates and
prompted banks to impose stricter loan requirements.
</P>
<P>
With crisis still far from over, automotive assemblers forecast
the sales to remain dismal for the remaining months of the year.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that the continued depreciation of the local
currency against the dollar could result in a new round of price
increase -- a scenario that could further discourage buyers.
</P>
</TEXT>
