<HEADLINE> US to Host Women Soccer Exhibition Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The United States will play
host to a Women's Cup soccer exhibition tournament featuring
South American champion Brazil, Russia and Mexico in September.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will be the last major women's soccer event in A
merica before the 1999 quadrennial World Cup slated on June 19 to
July 10.
</P>
<P>
The United States, the Olympic champion, has planned two
foreign tours and 14 international exhibitions in 1999 before the
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
By winning the South American championship in March, Brazil
already has qualified for the 16-nation World Cup field while
Mexico enters CONCACAF qualifying later this month.
</P>
<P>
Russia is in second place in its European group, and already
has assured itself of at least entering the continent's playoffs
for a World Cup berth.
</P>
<P>
The four European group winners qualify automatically for the
World Cup while the four runners-up enter two-leg playoffs to
determine two others.
</P>
<P>
The United States will take on Mexico on September 12 to open
the tournament, and Brazil will play Russia three days later.
</P>
<P>
The four teams will gather in New York on September 18 for a
doubleheader with Mexico playing Brazil and the Americans facing
Russia.
</P>
<P>
The final games will take place in Virginia, two days later
with Mexico playing Russia and the United States taking on
Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
