<HEADLINE> Beijing Using World Bank Loans To Improve Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital plans to use
200 million U.S. dollars in World Bank loans for its second
phase of environmental improvements in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The money will mainly be used to improve air quality and build
two sewage treatment plants.
</P>
<P>
A Municipal Government official says that 115 million
U.S. dollars of that amount will be used to provide central
heating for 40 residential complexes and to make other heating
systems more energy-efficient.
</P>
<P>
Sixtyseven million U.S. dollars will be used in the two sewage
treatment plants, which will be able to handle 300,000 tons of
sewage daily.
</P>
<P>
About 10 million U.S. dollars will be used for 20 LPG stations
for motor vehicles and to convert 10,000 buses and taxis to LPG
gas.
</P>
<P>
Beijing will also use 15 million U.S. dollars for a smoke and
gas desulphurization project at the Shijingshan Power Plant.
</P>
<P>
About 5 million U.S. dollars will be used to purchase
environmental quality monitoring devices.  
</P>
