<HEADLINE> Shanghai's 'Dawn Project' Funds Disciplinary Bellwethers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The "Dawn Project," which
subsidizes promising young scholars at Shanghai-based colleges and
universities, has already proven its worth. The first group of 83
beneficiaries are becoming bellwethers of their respective
disciplines.
</P>
<P>
The "Dawn Project," jointly initiated by the Shanghai Municipal
Education Commission and the city's educational development
foundation in 1995, has injected more than 5 million yuan of aid
into 83 scientific projects headed by 83 young scholars with an
average age of 36.
</P>
<P>
With the project's assistance, these young scholars have been
credited with great achievements in their respective disciplines
and published 484 academic papers, many of which are considered
major breakthroughs by their foreign counterparts.
</P>
<P>
While some scholars link their achievements with the country's
economic construction, others voluntarily organize reporting
meetings to publicize their achievements among ordinary
residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
