<HEADLINE> Guangdong Police Seize Counterfeit Money from Taiwan Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police seized a Taiwan
ship attempting to smuggle more than 62 million yuan of
counterfeit money into south China's Guangdong Province, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Three men on board the ship and four others on a fishing boat
which met the ship have been detained by police.
</P>
<P>
Police were tipped that, on the night of July 24, a Taiwan ship
was scheduled to meet a local fishing boat near Jiazi Township,
Guangdong Province, and that the transactions might involve
smuggled goods.
</P>
<P>
At 4:35 a.m. on July 25 the Taiwan ship entered the area and
was soon surrounded by police boats. The men on the local fishing
boat attempted to flee but were captured.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer said that, including this case,
Guangdong's border inspection forces have stopped three attempts
to smuggle counterfeit money on Taiwan fishing boat since the
beginning of this year. In all, 166 million yuan of counterfeit
money has been confiscated. 
</P>
