<HEADLINE> Vialli to Sue Over Drugs Claim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Gianluca Vialli said on Thursday
that he will sue Zdenek Zeman after the Roma coach indirectly
linked him with drug-taking in the Italian league.
</P>
<P>
Zeman made the comments in an Italian magazine last week
claiming that drugs were rife in Serie A. And he said some
Juventus players had gained muscle mass surprisingly quickly.
</P>
<P>
But Vialli who spent four years with the Turin club before
joining Chelsea in 1996, said: "I will not speak in detail about
it as it has nothing to do with football.
</P>
<P>
