with the game. But I'm old enough and strong enough to handle it.
I just hope it will be cleared up soon.
</P>
<P>
"If someone has made a mistake then they must pay for it, but
it will not be me."
</P>
<P>
Italian striker Pierluigi Casiraghi, who arrived at Chelsea
this year from Rome club Lazio, also refuted Zeman's claims: "The
Roma manager has talked about doping but I do not believe that
would not help anyone's game," he said.
</P>
<P>
"He started talking about doping and now he has changed his
allegations to pharmaceutical substances. Some drugs are openly
available in supermarkets and as long as they are legal then I do
not see there being a problem. But I don't think there is any
problem with illegal drugs in Italy," he said. 
