happiness with the signing. He said: "When I began to play
soccer, my dream was to be national capped. After entering into
the national squad, my aim was to join a world-class team. With
the dream coming true today, I am confident that I could do my
bit to bring the Crystal Palace to the Premiership."
</P>
<P>
Crystal Palace manager Terry Venables said: "we have a good
deal to sign the two Chinese players. Both of them are very good."
</P>
<P>
