<HEADLINE> Overseas Enterprises Booming in Yantai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Yantai development zone in
east China's Shandong Province approved 27 overseas-funded
projects, with a total investment of 73.88 million U.S. dollars
during the January-June period, up 9 percent over the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
An official of the development zone said that the Southeast
Asian financial crisis has had little effect on Yantai.
</P>
<P>
The Yantai development zone is China's fourth largest after
those in Tianjin, Guangzhou and Dalian. It generated more than 3.5
billion yuan of total industrial output in the first half of 1998,
up 29 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Yantai development zone has invested more than 300,000 yuan
to improve the environment in the past three years, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment in 1985, the development zone has had
451 foreign-funded projects involving a total investment of 1.36
billion U.S. dollars. Of them, 25 have an investment of more than
20 million U.S. dollars each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
