<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jakarta Police Arrest 14 Suspected Instigators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Jakarta police arrested 14
people believed to have actively instigated lawlessness during the
riots in the Indonesian capital on May 14, Antara News Agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police were currently seeking 20 other suspects who were still
at large, Jakarta police spokesman Lt. Col. Edward Aritonang said.
</P>
<P>
Two others were already being intensively investigated on
similar suspicions, Aritonang said, adding that investigations
were also being made to identify the possible coordinators of the
riots.
</P>
<P>
The country saw the worst looting and rioting in decades in
Jakarta, Medan and Solo from May 13 to 15. More than 1,000 lives
were claimed, and thousands of buildings were looted, damaged or
burned during the rioting.
</P>
<P>
Aritonang said police had obtained clues about the identities
of the suspects from looters who had been caught red-handed.
</P>
<P>
The suspects who lived near the scenes could be sentenced to a
maximum of five years in jail, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
