<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tyson Withdraws New Jersey Boxing License Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson withdrew his
application for a New Jersey boxing license Thursday, one day
before regulators set to make a final decision on it.
</P>
<P>
"The message was from Mr. Tyson that he has decided to
withdraw his application, " Tyson's lawyer Anthony Fusco Jr said.
"He asked me to respect his wishes and not make any comment or
speculation. As his lawyer, I have to do that."
</P>
<P>
The state Athletic Control Board was scheduled to decide
Friday whether to allow Tyson to return. He was banned for an one
year after biting Evander Holyfield's ears during a title fight
in Las Vegas last June.
</P>
<P>
Tyson lost his temper at the end of a hearing on July 19. He
cursed in front of regulators and refused to read a closing
statement. Many people criticized Tyson for not applying for a
license in Nevada, the state that revoked Tyson's license on June
28, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
