<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances to ATP Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Top seed and defending
champion Pete Sampras of the United States scored straight set
victory to move into the quarterfinals of the 2.45 million U.S.
dollars ATP Championship on Thursday
</P>
<P>
Sampras, in his quest to reclaim the world No. 1 ranking,
outdueled compatriot Jan-Michael Gambill 7-6 (7-3), 6-3 in their
first career meeting. He had held serve throughout the match.
</P>
<P>
In the only third-round match involving two seeds, Petr Korda
of the Czech Republic, No. 3 seed, ousted No. 14 Goran Ivanisevic
of Croatia 5-7, 6-4, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
In other matches involving seeded players, Yevgeny Kafelnikov
of Russia beat Australia's Scott Draper 6-3, 6-3, and No. 8
Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands was beaten by American Vince
Spadea, who downed Andre Agassi of the United States yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Magnus Larsson posted a 6-4, 6-4 win over German
Tommy Haas, while Thomas Johansson of Sweden beat Jerome Golmard
of Franch 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-2).
</P>
<P>
Tonight, fifth seed Patrick Rafter of Australia meets Todd
Martin of the United States, who dispatched 1997 finalist Thomas
Muster of Austria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
