<HEADLINE> F.A. Lifts Ban on Nicholson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The English Football Association
(F.A.) confirmed on Thursday that it had lifted a ban on former
West Bromwich Albion player Shane Nicholson, who was tested
positive last year.
</P>
<P>
Nicholson, who was tested positive for amphetamines after a
first division match in October, 1997, was banned indefinitely by
the F.A. in November.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old, who admitted using drugs for recreational
purposes for several years, was later sacked by West Brom.
</P>
<P>
An F.A. spokeswoman said on Thursday the ban had been lifted
after Nicholson had undergone rehabilitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
