<HEADLINE> Levski Sofia Produce Most Goals in Cup Winners's Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Levski Sofia produced the most
goals in the European Cup Winners' Cup qualifying round on
Thursday when they hammered Lokomotiv Vitebsk of Belarus 8-1 in
the first leg tie in front of 10,000 home fans.
</P>
<P>
Georgi Borisov hit a hat-trick and 23-year-old Bulgarian
international striker Georgi Ivanov finished with two but Levksi
finished the tie on a sour note when they were reduced to 10 men
following the sending-off of Krasimir Dimitrov in the 80th minute.
</P>
<P>
Levski lifted their 23rd Bulgarian Cup last May.
</P>
<P>
Rapid Bucharest fired home five goals in an 18-minute spell in
the second half on their way to beating Grevenmacher 6-2 in
Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
Danish side FC Copenhagen looked like reaching double figures
in their tie against Karabagh Agdam after hammering six goals
past their Azerbaijani opponents inside the opening 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Karabagh got their defence sorted out in the second half,
however, and managed to keep a clean sheet for the final 50
minutes to walk away 6-0 losers.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, all six goals in the Latvian city of Liepaja came
in the final 30 minutes, Metalurgs Liepaja beat Keflavik of
Iceland 4-2. Rolands Bulders hit a hat-trick.
</P>
<P>
In Tirana, Belgian side Genk recovered from an early goal by
Albania's Apolonia Fier to emerge 5-1 winners.
</P>
<P>
Lausanne Sports beat Amenia's Tsement Ararat by the same
scoreline at home, Swiss international midfielder Fabio Celestini
leading the onslaught with four goals.
</P>
<P>
One of European soccer's fallen giants, Partizan Belgrade kept
alive their hopes of shining once again on the big stage with a
2-0 win over Dynamo Batumi of Georgia.
</P>
<P>
Lee Makel scored the only goal in Hearts' victory over Latvian
side Lantana Tallinn to give the Scottish club a valuable away
goal going into the return clash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
