<HEADLINE> Fujian Plans 20 Electronics, Information Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
plans to build 20 key projects with a total investment of 17
billion yuan in the electronics and information industries in the
next few years, according to You Xiansheng, director of the
provincial electronics industry department.
</P>
<P>
The 20 projects include such fields as digital video and audio
products, artificial crystals, optical lenses and color scanners,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
You said his province, which faces Taiwan across the straits,
intends to attract investment from large overseas banks as well as
loans from foreign governments and banks. Some large enterprises
also will be encouraged to issue shares and bonds to raise funds,
he said.
</P>
<P>
When all 20 projects are completed, 35.5 billion yuan will be
added to the annual output value of the industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fujian is one of the largest electronics manufacturers in
China. Last year, the local electronics industry generated 27.28
billion yuan in output value, up 55 percent over the previous
year, with its gross profits growing by 77 percent to 1.44 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000), the province
will try to build six electronics and information industrial
centers in the cities of Fuzhou, Xiamen, Quanzhou and Zhangzhou.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
