<HEADLINE> Billiards World Contest Starts in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The best billiards
players of the world have gathered in this capital to take part
in a tournament being held August 12 to 17 in the Gonzalez
Jimenex de Quezada convention center.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by the president of the Colombian
Federation of Billiards, Pedro Gonzalez, at a press conference in
the Tequendama Hotel of Bogota, who added that this is the first
time Colombia organizes a billiards world contest, with the
sponsorship of a local brewery.
</P>
<P>
The press conference was attended also by the president of the
World Billiards Union, Spaniard Jorge Fuster, and the Number One
and Number Two billiard players of the world: Dutch Dick Jaspers,
and Swedish Torbjorn Blomdahl, besides Belgian Raymond Ceulemans,
many times world champion, and better known as "the father of
billiards."
</P>
<P>
According to Gonzalez, of the 76 sportsmen (70 Colombians and
6 from South America, Mexico and the United States) 12 will be
classified to dispute against 20 European players the world
ranking this Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Fuster, who made a big effort to bring to Colombia the best
players of the world, told Xinhua that for China to advance in
this discipline, it is necessary to prepare the players when they
are 13 or 14 years old in sports schools.
</P>
<P>
It is also necessary to organize more international
tournaments for the Chinese players to have more opportunities to
play against the Euroepans, the best of the world, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
