<HEADLINE> Donors In Southwestern China Aid Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 14 (Xinhua)-- Wang Shuang, a sixth-grader at a
school in Sichuan's provincial capital, Chengdu, became the first
person to donate to the flood relief fund when the Provincial
Civil Affairs Department opened its doors to the public on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A Department official said that by Wednesday morning the
largest donation of materials had come from the Chengdu Hongqi
Department Store, which gave 100,000 yuan worth of food and
clothing, and the largest money donation, from the Sichuan Guotai
Securities Corporation, which gave 100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is located on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River,
and is one of the worst flood-hit areas. There are reports of
16.31 million people in 154 counties having been affected, with
314 dead and 1,325 injured. More than 120,000 people have lost
their homes and are waiting to be relocated.
</P>
<P>
The Department says that half the relief funds and materials
will be sent to the worst-hit areas in four provinces along the
middle reaches of the Yangtze and the other half to local areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
