<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Thursday announced the approval of a 25
million U.S. dollar loan to Guatemala to help finance a reform of
the judicial sector.
</P>
<P>
The reform initiative will improve efficiency and facilitate
public access to justice as well as foster institutional
coordination within the judicial system sector, by employing an
integrated and sector-wide approach.
</P>
<P>
