<HEADLINE> Dow Falls Again, Giving up Wednesday's Gain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street fell
Thursday, but the market held ground in the face of another day of
panicky selling overseas.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average gave back an early 50-point
gain and fell 93.46 to close at 8,459.50. It lost 112 points
Tuesday and added 90 points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip gauge has now lost 878 points in a monthlong
slide from July 17's record of 9,337.97.
</P>
<P>
Other major stock indicators also suffered losses Thursday. But
Thursday's repeated plunge in Hong Kong and Russia failed to
rattle Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 9.31 to 1,074.91, and the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 22.99 to 1,802.54.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-3 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where composite volume totaled 782.51 million
shares, down from a brisk 842.81 million on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 4.40 to 541.06, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index fell 1.02 to 667.78.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 4.72 to 403.83.
