<HEADLINE> Customs Staff to be Rewarded for "Exceptional Captures" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Customs staff in Romania will
be rewarded if they discover drugs, weapons and national heritage
objects, provided a government decision taken on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the methods for collecting and using funds aimed
at rewarding the customs staff, those seizing "exceptional
captures" such as drugs, weapons and national heritage objects,
will be awarded considerable sums amounting up to ten percent of
the value of the seized goods, Nini Sapunaru, the manager of the
Customs General Directorate told the press during a briefing
following a Government meeting.
</P>
<P>
Customs staff will be granted such incentives to compensate for
their low monthly incomes that range between 600,000 and 1,600,000
lei (69 to 184 U.S. dollars), Sapunaru stressed.
</P>
<P>
The incentives fund aimed at the customs staff will also
include 35 percent of the value of the seized goods plus the fines
imposed during the customs checkings, Sapunaru said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
