<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Approves $55 Million Aid to Haiti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Thursday announced the approval of 55
million U.S. dollars in financing to Haiti for improving potable
water and sanitation services in the country.
</P>
<P>
The fund will also be used in establishing a regulatory
framework for the development of a waste water service, said the
IDB in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The IDB financing includes a 54 million U.S. dollars loan from
the Fund for Special Operations and a 965,000 U.S. dollars grant
in technical cooperation from the Multilateral Investment Fund.
</P>
<P>
The program will be carried out by the Haiti Ministry of Public
Works, Transport and Communications, Sector Reform Unit.
</P>
<P>
The IDB loan is for a 40-year term, and a five-year grace
period, and a one percent annual interest rate during the first 10
years and a two percent rate thereafter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
