<HEADLINE> Britain to Help Zimbabwe Set up Privatization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean and British
governments Thursday signed an agreement under which Britain
would provide about 3.9 million U.S. Dollars in support of the
establishment of privatization agency in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
"The setting up of a privatization agency will facilitate the
speeding up of the privatization and commercialization process of
public enterprises which currently has lagged behind other
economic targets," said Zimbabwe's Industry and Commerce Minister
Nathan Shamuyarira.
</P>
<P>
The agency would also provide technical and managerial support
to improve economic efficiency through enhanced output from the
privatized and commercialized public enterprises, he said.
</P>
<P>
The process was expected to raise revenue for the country and
enhance participation of indigenous people in the country's
economy, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
