<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Inspects Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called on civilians and soldiers to make greater efforts to fight
a final triumphant battle against the Yangtze River flooding.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China
Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military Commission,
arrived in central China's Hubei Province this morning amid high
temperatures to inspect the flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
He extended his best wishes and highest regards to all those
fighting on the anti-flood front, amd pointed out that continuing
and concerted efforts, as well as strong belief, will surely bring
final victory over the flood.
</P>
<P>
The Party Central Committee with Jiang at the core has shown
great concern about the severe flooding along the Yangtze River
and other watersheds which has been occurring since mid-June, and
has asked many times about the flood situations, and issued
several major decisions in the effort.
</P>
<P>
On the night of August 7, as the country's flood situation came
to the crucial point, Jiang presided over a Standing Committee
meeting of the CPC Central Committee, and made important
decisions.
</P>
<P>
At 10 am this morning, shortly after his plane landed, Jiang
went directly to the 300-kilometer-long Jingjiang Embankment,
which is thought to be the most dangerous of the Yangtze dikes,
having remained waterlogged for more than a month. However, tens
of thousands of civilians and soldiers have secured the embankment
despite one flood crest after another.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang witnessed the fifth raging Yangtze flood crest
which was passing Shashi at the time. The peak was measured at
44.83 meters with a flow rate of 49,500 cubic meters per second,
the largest this year. He felt a bit relieved when he learned that
the Guanyinji, the weakest point of the embankment, had been
reinforced.
</P>
<P>
This afternoon, Jiang hurried to Honghu, whose
135-kilometer-long embankment is the weakest section of the
Jingjiang embankment. Jiang called out to the flood-fighters that
a great victory has been achieved so far to protect the Yangtze
embankments and major cities, but vigilance is all the more
important at a time when the floodwaters are beginning to recede.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the People's Liberation Army, and said he
hopes the 130,000 soldiers participating in flood control along
the Yangtze River will continue their efforts and stick to the end.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was accompanied by Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao, who is also
head of the State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters,
Vice-Chairman of the Central Military Commission Zhang Wannian,
and Zeng Qinghong, director of the General Office of the CPC
Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
