<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Tumbles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange
National-100 Index went down to 3,311.60 points Thursday, by
falling 242.91 points, or 6.76 percent, from that of Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The value stood at over 67 trillion Turkish Liras (over 247
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The financial index fell 319.01 points, or 7.35 percent, to
close at 4,001.45 points. The industrial index plunged 179.63
points, or 5.80 percent, to close at 2,887.23 and the service
index went down 291.76 points, or 6.37 percent, to close at
4,219.17 points from Wednesday's closings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
