<HEADLINE> International Seminar on Kashmir Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A two-day international
seminar on Kashmir ended Thursday with a call for the resolution
of the dispute in accordance with U.N. resolutions and the
aspirations of the Kashmiri people for peace and security in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The seminar in Muzaffarabad, capital of Azad Jammu and Kashmir
(Pak-held Kashmir), was organized by the Pakistani Ministry of
Information in collaboration with the parliamentary Kashmir
Committee and Azad Jammu and Kashmir University.
</P>
<P>
Intellectuals, experts on defense and regional and
international affairs analysts from Pakistan and other countries
stressed the different dimensions and aspects of the Kashmir
dispute with special reference to U.N. resolutions on Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Speakers at the seminar were of the view that the solution of
the Kashmir dispute is vital to ensuring peace and security in the
world in general and South Asia in particular. 
</P>
</TEXT>
