<HEADLINE> Japan Helps Angola with $6.5m in Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government is to
donate about 6.5 million U.S. Dollars to help the country improve
the road system in the capital city Luanda.
</P>
<P>
Manuel Antonio Paulo, official with the Public Works and Urban
Planning Ministry, said Thursday that the money would be used to
rebuild the major roads in Luanda, one of the biggest cities in
Africa, with three million people.
</P>
<P>
Japan donated medical equipment worth 1.5 million Dollars in
March this year.  
</P>
