<HEADLINE> Nigeria Develops Master Plan for Drug Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has developed a master
plan for decisive control of drug abuse, the official News Agency
of Nigeria (NAN) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the master plan, developed with assistance
from the United Nations International Drug Abuse Control Program
(UNDCP), will be released before the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Shariq Bin Raza, representative of the UNDCP in
Nigeria, as saying that the master plan "aims to primarily
coordinate efforts to tackle drug problems through the
participation of the government, the non-governmental
organizations and the general public."
</P>
<P>
The U.N. official regretted that drug control efforts in
Nigeria had been compounded by lack of assistance from external
donors owing to the political situation in Nigeria, its size,
population and the prevailing socio-economic environment.
</P>
<P>
He, however, expressed the confidence that with political will
and commitment, enhanced awareness, better planning with
appropriate institutions, structures and legislations put in
place, Nigeria will be able to rid of drug abuse. 
</P>
