<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Needs 400,000 Tons of Fertilizers Next </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The National Fertilizer
Industry Agency of Ethiopia said Thursday that the nation needs
432,000 tons of fertilizers for the next production year.
</P>
<P>
Half of the stated sum is obtained in donation, said Tebebu
Haile, head of the market assessment and development department
of the agency.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Haile as saying that Ethiopia
spends 85 million U.S. Dollars annually for the purchase of
fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
According to Haile, the agency has signed a loan agreement
with the World Bank for the purchase of fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
A loan agreement has also been reached with the African
Development Bank for the purchase of 50,000 tons of fertilizers
for the coming three years.
</P>
<P>
Some 30,000 tons of fertilizers will also be bought with the
financial aid secured from the government of the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia bought over 485, 000 tons of fertilizers this year
and about 270,000 tons have been distributed.
</P>
<P>
The fertilizer consumption in Ethiopia has now grown
remarkably especially over the past six years, Haile said, adding
that only 35 percent of the total population of farmers in
Ethiopia use fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
In Ethiopia, only 17 kilograms of fertilizer is used per
hectare while 98 kilograms of the input is used per hectare in
developed countries, the head added, 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
